Pink Floyd - Another Brick In The Wall, Part 2 (Song with Solo)

2/14/17: My chord tab is a basic presentation for those who
want to quickly learn the song. It's obvious where they're
played. Throw in some open Dm, F, C and G chords in
place of the same barre chords at your discretion for fun
since both are overlapped in the song's multi tracking.

Most people want an accurate solo tab so I've created one.
I scoured the Internet for a perfect solo tab and was
frustrated that one didn't already exist to do this great 
classic the justice it deserves. Most were close but none
as spot on as I wanted so I spent a few hours painstakingly
creating my own. I modified the four-fret bends with easier 
ways to play the parts that sound the same. A few parts
in the solo were difficult to interpret because of the 
poor digital sound quality online and the multi-tracking, 
effects and distortion of Gilmour's guitars. But I think
that I've nailed it. Many thanks for your 5-star ratings!
12/19/17: added alternate form of G vamp chord.

Standard Tuning: EADGBe

